bio.experienceSummary:
Hi! My name is Maya and I am so excited to meet you! I am a compassionate, reliable, and active nanny with 8+ years of professional experience. I have a Bachelor's degree in Social Work with a concentration in Early Childhood Development. I have experience caring for children of all ages (newborn - 10+ years old), and I find such joy in creating a caring environment that is safe, healthy, nurturing, and fun. I believe in the gentle parenting philosophy, and I love helping children learn through their natural interests such as exploring nature, arts, cooking, and building just to name a few. 

When I am not supporting families I am usually taking a walk and enjoying some sun, or trying new recipes in the kitchen.

Providing childcare for the past 8 years has been a wonderful experience! I've been honored to support many families and children , and I look forward to continuing this journey and creating new experiences with the next family that I am paired with.

As a childcare provider, my passion lies in nurturing the growth and development of young minds. With two years of experience as a caregiver, I strive to make a positive impact on the lives of children while supporting families with a reliable childcare option. My patient and calm demeanor, coupled with my creative and imaginative nature, allows me to foster a friendly and approachable environment for the children in my care.

I prioritize open communication with parents, providing verbal updates at pickup and regular updates via text or phone call, ensuring that parents are always informed about their child's day and any issues that arise. Regarding household rules, I firmly believe in following the parents' lead, respecting their parenting style and expectations.

When it comes to engaging with children, I enjoy a variety of games, from outdoor sports and physical games that encourage activity to board games and puzzles that stimulate their minds.

I used to live in Northern Virginia and worked for The Country Day School as a teacher. My first year as a teacher was ages 2-3 and my second year was ages 4-6. They did swim instruction, non confrontational de-escalation of arguments, worked with kids on the spectrum and much more. I was CPR, First Aid and Bodily Fluid Cleanup Certified and will redo any qualifications needed or wanted.

My love for children roots back to my love for small things, like animals, plants or even mere toys. No matter the case, I felt the urgency to protect, love and nourish these things. As I grew older, this carried over to my love for kids; like when I was younger, I felt the urgency to protect, love and nourish children. Not only do I feel this way about children from all ages, I get a genuine happiness out of them I truly love being around kids. For those reasons it makes it a so easy for me to work in childcare.
I have extensive childcare experience, with children aged 0 to 13. From August 2022 to current time. I worked with children in various age groups, including infants 0-2, preschoolers 2-5, and school-aged kids 6-9. I have 1980 hours of infant care as a nursery teacher. From January to June 2024, I worked as an english teacher for ages 10 to 13, providing daily care and education.

description.originalText: She looked after my twins. Brilliantly. She got them ready for school, took them to school came back cleaned up, got them from school, made dinner. She did everything!

bio.experienceSummary: I have paid experience with a new born and toddler (2 months job) as well as taking care/babysitting of many young family members (new borns to young teenagers)

As a caregiver, my passion lies in nurturing children's growth and making a positive impact on their young lives. With one year of experience, I bring patience, creativity, and a friendly demeanor to my interactions with children. I believe in open communication with parents, ensuring they're informed about their child's day and any concerns that arise, using their preferred method of contact.

My comfort level with enforcing household rules is high, as I understand the importance of structure and consistency in a child's life. When it comes to playtime, I enjoy engaging children in outdoor sports, board games, puzzles, and educational games that stimulate learning.

I'm proficient in English, and I'm happy to assist with cooking, meal preparation, light housekeeping, and supervising swimming activities.

I'm eager to connect with families who share my values and approach to childcare.

For over 10 years I've worked with children ages 0-18. From babysitting to substitute teaching, I've had several experiences working with the youth. I sing and act with children. If you need a sitter that will engage with the children with puppet shows, songs, crafts, and cooking fun I am definitely the person for the job. I am also a certified tutor to math, reading, science, english, and computer courses. I taught summer reading courses, former substitute teacher and a youth volunteer. In addition to the mentioned skills I am a trained singer/ voice coach. I am open to doing light house work and cooking. I hosted a cooking show during my years as a college undergraduate and working on a children's educational pilot. A background check is available and I'd love to help with your needs!

Hello wonderful families!
I'm Agnes. Currently working with a family whose contract is about to end and I'm looking for my next long term family. My experience with kids has been private nanny/babysitter for 6 years, working at the pediatric emergency unit for 2 years, and a volunteer Sunday school teacher for 2 years. I have experience with almost all ages from newborns to age 17 including special needs. Multiples including twin babies.

My philosophy on child rearing is to encourage a child's natural curiosity for the world while giving them structure and a safe space to grow and learn.

A highly motivated Nanny/Child Care professional, extremely detail-oriented and have the ability to work well with others, and independently. Proficient in time management and organizational skills, as well as thorough in completing a task in a timely manner. A responsible and dedicated individual who is motivated to move ahead into the future.

description.originalText: Agnes took great care of my 4 month old baby. Additionally, when I got home, all baby chores were done including washing, dying and folding clothes, cleaning and sterilizing bottles, and more. She communicates well and always kept me abreast of any changes. We will certainly love to use her long term.

bio.experienceSummary: I have a strong passion for children since my own childhood. I like spending time with them, helping them with things and gaining more knowledge about them due to which I did a Montessori course from AMI.

description.originalText: Aisha is an experienced child care professional who emits a warm, caring and calming vibe that my kids are eased by. She brought an activity to the first visit to help break the ice. I can trust that she will be able to get through dinner, bath time, and bed time without fuss and that the kids will be asleep when we come home. She is punctual and clear with communication.

bio.experienceSummary: I have been babysitting since I was 13 years old. I started to professionally nanny at 20, I am now 32. I am the eldest of eight kids. (the newest Circa 2019) I absolutely love children and I would love to continue helping families with each of their specific needs. I have really great references, I am extremely responsible. I am CPR/First Aid certified And I am in good health and vaccinated. I have extensive knowledge in caring for infants and newborns. I worked at Northside on the mother/baby unit and that parlayed into night-nannying; putting newborns on sleep cycles so that the parents can get to sleep. I have an Early Childhood Education Degree from AMC. I also have another degree in Linguistics from GSU. I am also punctual, hard-working, detail-oriented, trustworthy and honest. I am very tolerant, patient, and kind. I can manage a class of 20 kids. I used to teach K-2nd grade.

description.displayText: Shay nannied our twin girls from the age of 1 month to 14 months. She started helping us as a night nanny, an then transitioned to day times. As a night nanny, she was always prompt and helpful in sleep training. As our full-time day nanny, Shay has created a really special relationship with our girls. She is extremely calm, and she takes direct feedback well. Taking care of infant twins is not an easy job. I respect the work Shay does greatly!
